-- UniCredit Is in Negotiations to Buy Poland's Bank Millennium, Puls Says
-- Maciej Martewicz
-- 2010-07-14T05:40:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/unicredit-is-in-talks-to-buy-poland-s-bank-millennium-puls-biznesu-says.html

          
          
             UniCredit SpA of Italy is in talks 
with Banco Comercial Portugues SA to buy Poland’s Bank 
Millennium SA, Puls Biznesu reported, without saying where it 
got the information.  
 Arkadiusz Mierzwa, a spokesman for Bank Pekao SA, 
UniCredit’s Polish unit, declined to comment when reached by 
phone by Bloomberg News today.  
 Sofia Raposo, head of investor-relations of Banco 
Commercial, didn’t answer a call to her office outside business
hours. Wojciech Kaczorowski, Millennium’s spokesman, had no 
immediate comment.  
